
BUSINESS PROBLEM

In many organizations, onboarding and offboarding are repetitive, manual processes that can lead to:

Delays in providing access to new employees.
Human error when assigning permissions or licenses.
Security risks caused by inactive accounts remaining enabled.
Inconsistent documentation and audit trails.
Increased workload for IT support teams.

This project demonstrates how automation can improve efficiency, standardize administrative tasks, and reduce operational risk.

OBJECTIVES

The project aims to:

Automate user provisioning using PowerShell.
Reduce manual administrative tasks.
Standardize onboarding and offboarding procedures.
Improve security by ensuring timely account deactivation.
Generate logs for auditing and troubleshooting.
Demonstrate practical Microsoft 365 administration skills.
Showcase scripting and automation capabilities relevant to IT Support and Systems Administration roles.

Key Features
Employee Onboarding
Import new employee information from a CSV file.
Create Microsoft 365 user accounts.
Assign licenses based on department or role.
Add users to security groups and distribution lists.
Configure mailbox settings.
Generate temporary passwords.
Record all actions in a log file.

Employee Offboarding
Disable user accounts.
Remove Microsoft 365 licenses.
Remove security group memberships.
Hide mailboxes from the Global Address List.
Configure email forwarding or mailbox conversion where required.
Generate an audit report detailing completed actions.

